"title": "7026: church, leadership of",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "7026",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Jesus Christ is the absolute head of the church. He sets leaders in the church to enable the whole church to grow into maturity. Christ's authority in the church is acknowledged more by the church's obedience to God than through any particular form of government.</p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ alone is head of the church</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col1:18\">COL 1:18</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt23:8-Matt23:10\">MAT 23:8–23:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph1:22\">EPH 1:22</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph4:15\">EPH 4:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph5:23\">EPH 5:23</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col2:19\">COL 2:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb3:3\">HEB 3:3</a></p>\n<h2>The Holy Spirit directs the church</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts13:2\">ACT 13:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts15:28\">ACT 15:28</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts16:6-Acts16:7\">ACT 16:6–16:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts20:28\">ACT 20:28</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom8:14\">ROM 8:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor12:11\">1CO 12:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev2:7\">REV 2:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev2:11\">REV 2:11</a></p>\n<h2>The appointment of leaders in the church</h2>\n<h3>God calls and equips leaders</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph4:11\">EPH 4:11</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt16:18\">MAT 16:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts1:24-Acts1:26\">ACT 1:24–1:26</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts9:15-Acts9:16\">ACT 9:15–9:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts20:28\">ACT 20:28</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts26:16-Acts26:18\">ACT 26:16–26:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor12:28\">1CO 12:28</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal1:15-Gal1:17\">GAL 1:15–1:17</a></p>\n<h3>Delegated leadership</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts6:3-Acts6:6\">ACT 6:3–6:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts14:23\">ACT 14:23</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Titus1:5\">TIT 1:5</a></p>\n<h3>The appointment of apostles</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark3:13-Mark3:19\">MRK 3:13–3:19</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt10:1-Matt10:4\">MAT 10:1–10:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke6:12-Luke6:16\">LUK 6:12–6:16</a> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor9:1-1Cor9:2\">1CO 9:1–9:2</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor3:3\">2CO 3:3</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph2:20\">EPH 2:20</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev21:14\">REV 21:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts2:42\">ACT 2:42</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts15:6\">ACT 15:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts15:22-Acts15:23\">ACT 15:22–15:23</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess2:6\">1TH 2:6</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Pet3:2\">2PE 3:2</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jude1:17\">JUD 1:17</a></p>\n<h3>Prophets as leaders</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts15:32\">ACT 15:32</a></strong> <em>Judas and Silas were leaders in the Jerusalem church (<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts15:22\">Ac 15:22</a>).</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts11:27-Acts11:30\">ACT 11:27–11:30</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts13:1-Acts13:2\">ACT 13:1–13:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom12:6\">ROM 12:6</a> <em>The role of prophets as leaders is distinct from the gift of prophecy, which was in principle available to all</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor12:28\">1CO 12:28</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor14:29-1Cor14:30\">1CO 14:29–14:30</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph3:5\">EPH 3:5</a></p>\n<h3>Evangelists as leaders</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts21:8\">ACT 21:8</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph4:11\">EPH 4:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim4:5\">2TI 4:5</a></p>\n<h3>Pastors and teachers as leaders</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts20:28\">ACT 20:28</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John21:15-John21:17\">JHN 21:15–21:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts13:1\">ACT 13:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom12:7\">ROM 12:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor12:28\">1CO 12:28</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim3:2\">1TI 3:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Titus1:9\">TIT 1:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas3:1\">JAS 3:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet5:2\">1PE 5:2</a> <em>Pastors are also called “shepherds”.</em></p>\n<h3>Elders as leaders</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim3:1\">1TI 3:1</a></strong> <em>“Elder” and “overseer” or “bishop” are more or less interchangeable.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts11:30\">ACT 11:30</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts14:23\">ACT 14:23</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts15:2\">ACT 15:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts15:22\">ACT 15:22</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts20:17\">ACT 20:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim5:17\">1TI 5:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Titus1:5\">TIT 1:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas5:14\">JAS 5:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2John1:1\">2JN 1:1</a></p>\n<h3>Deacons as leaders</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil1:1\">PHP 1:1</a></strong> <em>“Deacon” means “one who serves”.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts6:5-Acts6:6\">ACT 6:5–6:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim3:8\">1TI 3:8</a></p>\n<h2>Qualifications for church leadership</h2>\n<p>The first apostles were witnesses of Jesus Christ's life and resurrection:\n <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts1:21-Acts1:22\">ACT 1:21–1:22</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts10:41\">ACT 10:41</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor9:1-1Cor9:2\">1CO 9:1–9:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor15:7-1Cor15:8\">1CO 15:7–15:8</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Pet1:16\">2PE 1:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts6:3\">ACT 6:3</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim3:1-1Tim3:12\">1TI 3:1–3:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim5:17\">1TI 5:17</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Titus1:6-Titus1:9\">TIT 1:6–1:9</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet5:1-1Pet5:4\">1PE 5:1–5:4</a></p>\n<h2>Responsibilities of church leaders</h2>\n<h3>To preach the gospel</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom1:15\">ROM 1:15</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor1:17\">1CO 1:17</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal2:8\">GAL 2:8</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph3:8\">EPH 3:8</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim2:7\">1TI 2:7</a></p>\n<h3>To teach sound doctrine</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim4:6\">1TI 4:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim4:13\">1TI 4:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim5:17\">1TI 5:17</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb13:7\">HEB 13:7</a></p>\n<h3>To give direction in church life</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts15:2\">ACT 15:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts15:6\">ACT 15:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts15:22-Acts15:23\">ACT 15:22–15:23</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts16:4\">ACT 16:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts20:28-Acts20:31\">ACT 20:28–20:31</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim5:17\">1TI 5:17</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet5:2\">1PE 5:2</a></p>\n<h3>To be an example in loving service</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt20:26-Matt20:28\">MAT 20:26–20:28</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark10:43-Mark10:45\">MRK 10:43–10:45</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark9:35\">MRK 9:35</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John13:13-John13:15\">JHN 13:13–13:15</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb13:7\">HEB 13:7</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet5:3\">1PE 5:3</a></p>\n<h3>To train and appoint other leaders</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts14:23\">ACT 14:23</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim4:14\">1TI 4:14</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim2:2\">2TI 2:2</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Titus1:5\">TIT 1:5</a></p>\n<h3>To pray for the sick</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas5:14\">JAS 5:14</a></p>\n<h3>To exercise discipline in the church</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor13:10\">2CO 13:10</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess5:12\">1TH 5:12</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim1:20\">1TI 1:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim5:20\">1TI 5:20</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Titus3:10\">TIT 3:10</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/3John1:10\">3JN 1:10</a></p>\n<h2>The church's responsibilities to its leaders</h2>\n<h3>To respect and submit to its leaders</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts16:4\">ACT 16:4</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess5:12-1Thess5:13\">1TH 5:12–5:13</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim5:19\">1TI 5:19</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb13:17\">HEB 13:17</a></p>\n<h3>To pray for its leaders</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph6:19\">EPH 6:19</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess5:25\">1TH 5:25</a></p>\n<h3>To support its leaders financially</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor9:7-1Cor9:14\">1CO 9:7–9:14</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil4:15-Phil4:19\">PHP 4:15–4:19</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim5:17-1Tim5:18\">1TI 5:17–5:18</a></p>\n<h2>The corporate government of the church</h2>\n<h3>In choosing leaders</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts6:3-Acts6:6\">ACT 6:3–6:6</a></p>\n<h3>In implementing decisions</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts15:22-Acts15:29\">ACT 15:22–15:29</a></p>\n<h3>In building up the church</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom12:4-Rom12:8\">ROM 12:4–12:8</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor12:4-1Cor12:12\">1CO 12:4–12:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor12:27\">1CO 12:27</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph4:3\">EPH 4:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph4:7-Eph4:16\">EPH 4:7–4:16</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet4:10-1Pet4:11\">1PE 4:10–4:11</a></p>\n<h3>In discerning true and false teachings</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John4:1-1John4:3\">1JN 4:1–4:3</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2John1:10\">2JN 1:10</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev2:2\">REV 2:2</a></p>\n<h3>In exercising discipline</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt18:15-Matt18:20\">MAT 18:15–18:20</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor5:4-1Cor5:5\">1CO 5:4–5:5</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor2:6-2Cor2:8\">2CO 2:6–2:8</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Thess3:14-2Thess3:15\">2TH 3:14–3:15</a></p>\n<h2>The structure of the church</h2>\n<h3>The pattern of church life</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts2:42\">ACT 2:42</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts2:46\">ACT 2:46</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts5:42\">ACT 5:42</a></p>\n<h3>The house church</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts1:13-Acts1:14\">ACT 1:13–1:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts12:12\">ACT 12:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts16:40\">ACT 16:40</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom16:5\">ROM 16:5</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor16:19\">1CO 16:19</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col4:15\">COL 4:15</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phlm1:2\">PHM 1:2</a></p>\n<h3>The local church</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts13:1\">ACT 13:1</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom16:1\">ROM 16:1</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor1:2\">1CO 1:2</a> <em>It is unknown whether there were subdivisions of the church in towns such as Corinth</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess1:1\">1TH 1:1</a></p>\n<h3>Churches in a region</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts9:31\">ACT 9:31</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts15:41\">ACT 15:41</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor16:1\">1CO 16:1</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor8:1\">2CO 8:1</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal1:2\">GAL 1:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal1:22\">GAL 1:22</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev1:4\">REV 1:4</a> <em>Normally the NT speaks of “churches” in an area rather than of a unified regional structure.</em></p>\n<h3>The universal church</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt16:18\">MAT 16:18</a></strong> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor12:28\">1CO 12:28</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph1:22\">EPH 1:22</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph3:10\">EPH 3:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph5:25\">EPH 5:25</a></p>",
